FBIS3-37622 "drsov035_s_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 Georgia Abkhaz Armed Forces on `Highest Level' of Readiness LD1802141594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1350 GMT 18 Feb 94 LD1802141594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] [Text] Moscow, 18 Feb -- The highest level of combat readiness was declared today in the Abkhazian Armed Forces. According to a report of the press service of an authorized spokesman of the Abkhazian republic in Russia, this is in connection with the active regrouping of Georgian troops on the Georgia-Abkhazia border along the Inguri River. According to the same information, early this morning the Coast Guard forces of Galskiy Rayon averted an attempted landing by Georgian assault forces. The Abkhazian Defense Ministry believes that there is still a danger of an incursion by subversive groups.
